  "text": "XTEN technology may represent an opportunity to optimize the glucagon peptide for prophylactic applications. The XTEN sequence has been demonstrated to controllably increase the serum half-life of peptides and proteins [CITATION_1] . In addition, fusion of the XTEN sequence can increase the solubility and stability of the attached peptide, while simultaneously enabling recombinant production and improved manufacturing. The XTEN sequence has been shown to be safe and poorly immunogenic in a number of animal species. We therefore constructed a series of glucagon-XTEN fusion constructs (Gcg-XTEN) to assess the in vivo effects of extended glucagon exposure.",
